<section xml:id="C18.S20">
<title>Hahn Class: Explicit Representations</title>        
 
<subsection xml:id="C18.S20.SS1">
<title>Rodrigues Formulas</title>        
 
  
<para xml:id="C18.S20.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C18.S20.SS1.p1.s1">
For comments on the use of the forward-difference operator <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.SS1.p1.m1">\Delta_{x}</Math> , the backward-difference operator <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.SS1.p1.m2">\nabla_{x}</Math> , and the central-difference operator <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.SS1.p1.m3">\delta_{x}</Math> , see §18.2(ii).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C18.S20.Px1">
<title>Hahn, Krawtchouk, Meixner, and Charlier</title>   
<para xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="18.20.1" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S20.E1">p_{n}(x)=\frac{1}{\kappa_{n}w_{x}}\nabla_{x}^{n}\left(w_{x}\prod_{\ell=0}^{n-1 }F(x+\ell)\right), if x\in X</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.s2">
In (18.20.1)
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.s3">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.m1">X</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.m2">w_{x}</Math> are as in Table 18.19.1.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.s4">
For the Hahn polynomials <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.m3">p_{n}(x)=Q_{n}\left(x;\alpha,\beta,N\right)</Math> and <Math equation-number="18.20.2" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S20.E2">F(x)=(x+\alpha+1)(x-N),\kappa_{n}={\left(-N\right)_{n}}{\left(\alpha+1\right)_{n}}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.s5">
For the Krawtchouk, Meixner, and Charlier polynomials, <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.m4">F(x)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S20.Px1.p1.m5">\kappa_{n}</Math> are as in Table 18.20.1.
</sentence>

</para>
         
